<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<!--
  KelpieHelper is the CEF (Chromium Embedded Framework) subprocess. CEF spawns
  multiple helper processes per browser (Renderer, GPU, Plugin, Alerts) by
  re-launching this executable with different command-line switches.

  Each entitlement below is required by Chromium's subprocess model:

  - allow-jit: V8 generates and executes JIT machine code at runtime. Without
    this, every JS evaluation traps as W^X violation under hardened runtime.
  - allow-unsigned-executable-memory: Chromium maps JIT pages as RWX before
    transitioning them to RX. Hardened runtime blocks the initial allocation
    unless this is set.
  - disable-library-validation: CEF and its helper bundles ship as ad-hoc
    signed (`codesign -s -`) frameworks loaded from the app's Frameworks
    directory at runtime. Library validation refuses to load any framework
    that wasn't signed with the same Team ID as the host binary. Until we ship
    a notarised, fully Apple-signed CEF distribution, this stays on.
  - network.client: CEF subprocesses connect back to the parent via the Mach
    rendezvous server; the GPU helper also opens local sockets.

  To verify these are still needed:
    1. Comment one out, rebuild, then launch Kelpie and switch the renderer to
       Chromium via the toolbar.
    2. The helper will fail to launch and Console.app will log a clear
       sandbox/codesign rejection naming the missing entitlement.
    3. Re-enable and rebuild before committing.

  Do NOT add any of these to the main app's `Kelpie.entitlements`. The host
  process has no JIT or unsigned-library needs; only the CEF subprocess does.
-->
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
